WEBVTT

00:00:01.080 --> 00:00:01.400
Alright!

00:00:01.640 --> 00:00:03.880
Your app is live and backed up, now let's make

00:00:03.880 --> 00:00:04.840
sure it stays healthy.

00:00:05.804 --> 00:00:08.524
The CLI gives you a full picture of any

00:00:08.524 --> 00:00:11.484
server from your laptop. Three angles to check

00:00:12.124 --> 00:00:14.684
: system health, running containers, and

00:00:14.684 --> 00:00:16.364
the repositories themselves.

00:00:19.831 --> 00:00:22.631
Let us start with the system view. The machine query

00:00:22.631 --> 00:00:25.831
command with the system filter shows uptime, disk

00:00:25.831 --> 00:00:27.751
usage, and storage status.

00:00:27.955 --> 00:00:30.835
Uptime, disk, storage. Everything you

00:00:30.835 --> 00:00:31.635
need at a glance.

00:00:35.108 --> 00:00:37.988
Now containers. This view lists every running

00:00:37.988 --> 00:00:40.708
container across every repository on the machine

00:00:40.948 --> 00:00:43.908
: name, status, health, CPU

00:00:44.068 --> 00:00:46.628
, memory, plus which repo owns each

00:00:46.628 --> 00:00:46.948
one.

00:00:47.150 --> 00:00:49.710
Every container across every repo

00:00:49.870 --> 00:00:50.830
, in one view.

00:00:54.193 --> 00:00:56.993
And the repos themselves. Size, mount

00:00:56.993 --> 00:00:59.793
status, Docker daemon status, disk

00:01:01.233 --> 00:01:03.793
usage. Everything you need to know about each isolated environment.

00:01:03.911 --> 00:01:06.551
All repos, all their daemons, all their

00:01:06.551 --> 00:01:07.671
disk usage.

00:01:11.070 --> 00:01:13.710
The machine query command with no filters gives you

00:01:13.790 --> 00:01:16.430
everything in one shot. System info

00:01:16.750 --> 00:01:19.630
, containers, repositories, all together.

00:01:19.743 --> 00:01:22.223
Everything together, no filter needed.

00:01:25.673 --> 00:01:28.553
And finally the diagnostic check for a local sanity

00:01:28.553 --> 00:01:31.753
check on your laptop. Node, SSH

00:01:32.473 --> 00:01:35.913
key, renet, Docker. All the things the CLI itself depends on. That is the full series. From install to mon

00:01:38.153 --> 00:01:40.713
itoring, all from your terminal.

00:01:40.902 --> 00:01:43.622
All green means your local CLI is healthy.

00:01:44.426 --> 00:01:46.259
You can now install,

00:01:46.259 --> 00:01:46.717
configure,

00:01:46.717 --> 00:01:47.175
deploy,

00:01:47.175 --> 00:01:47.633
fork,

00:01:47.633 --> 00:01:48.549
go live,

00:01:48.549 --> 00:01:49.007
autostart,

00:01:49.007 --> 00:01:49.923
back up,

00:01:49.923 --> 00:01:50.839
and monitor.

00:01:50.839 --> 00:01:53.130
The advanced track starts next:

00:01:53.130 --> 00:01:55.420
version your repos like code,

00:01:55.420 --> 00:01:57.252
with commits and rollbacks.
